citeinfo.title: Land_Use

descript.abstract: Land_Use is a polygon shapefile identifying land uses within the former Regional Municipality of Ottawa-Carleton. By identifying land uses in the urban areas, it is possible to determine the distribution and acreage of the best areas for each land use activity, and identify areas where land use conflicts may arise. Housing is the largest user of urban land in Ottawa, occupying nearly half of the urbanized area. Open space & recreation land, institutional land, industrial & utilities land, and commercial land follow respectively.
descript.supplinf: Data is provided 'as is' and the former RMOC makes no warranties as to the condition, quality or freedom from error of any dataset, or its fitness for a particular use. Carleton University Library has the most up to date geospatial files from the former RMOC. Please do not contact the City directly. If you need additional help with the data, contact the MADGIC reference desk. The original data was in MIF (MapInfo Interchange Format) - a straight translation from MIF to ArcView shapefiles was performed using MapInfo's Universal Translator module. Inconsistencies between file formats are due to the nature of their respective programs.
descript.purpose: Shows the various land usages within the former Regional Municipality of Ottawa-Carleton, excluding the Greenbelt. This digital data set is useful as a general base map on which you can plot your own features of interest or you may combine your own attribute data to link to specific features. MapInfo and ArcView mapping software also allows the user to perform simple selection and analysis of the data such as area and distance calculations, simple statistics and extracting data that meets specific criteria through the use of structured query language (SQL).
